devdoc.details: A smart contract to manage a trust-based gig economy system using escrow for payment and a one-sided reputation system (Contractor rates Worker). * This contract is the definitive, immutable source of truth for all gig states and handles all ETH transactions securely on the blockchain.

completeGig(uint256).details: Worker marks the gig as completed.

confirmGigAndPay(uint256).details: Contractor confirms the gig is complete and pays the worker (releases escrow). This is the core money transfer logic.

createGig(string,uint256).details: Contractor creates a new gig and sends the payment to the contract (escrow). The `payable` keyword is essential for receiving the ETH.

getGigStatus(uint256).details: Retrieves the current status of a gig.

getUserReputation(address).details: Calculates the average reputation score for a user.

rateUser(uint256,address,uint256).details: Allows only the Contractor to rate the Worker after a gig is paid.

registerUser(uint8).details: Allows a user to register as either a Contractor or a Worker. This function is typically called by the frontend or an authentication service.
